Items.Title: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the city of New York to prune trees, bushes and other vegetation that obstruct traffic control signals or devices.
Items.ActionText: This Introduction was Hearing Held by Committee
Items.MatterName: Requiring the city of New York to prune trees that block traffic signs or signals within three days of notification.
